    - Modifications (compared to the upstream OpenCV 4.13.0 release):
      The following files were modified to remove unused classes, methods,
      imports, and native declarations:
        * org.opencv.imgproc.Imgproc – Removed methods and native declarations
          for: LineSegmentDetector, GeneralizedHoughBallard/Guil, Moments,
          HuMoments, convexityDefects, minAreaRect, boxPoints, fitEllipse,
          fitEllipseAMS, fitEllipseDirect, getClosestEllipsePoints,
          rotatedRectangleIntersection, and RotatedRect-based ellipse overloads.
          Removed related enum constants (LSD_REFINE_*).
        * org.opencv.photo.Photo – Removed methods and native declarations for:
          createAlignMTB, createCalibrateDebevec, createCalibrateRobertson,
          createMergeDebevec, createMergeMertens, createMergeRobertson,
          createTonemap, createTonemapDrago, createTonemapMantiuk,
          createTonemapReinhard, and related imports.
        * org.opencv.utils.Converters – Removed conversion methods for:
          Point3, Rect2d, KeyPoint, DMatch, RotatedRect, and their
          corresponding MatOf* types.
      The following 64 unused Java source files were deleted entirely
      (complete packages org.opencv.video, org.opencv.videoio, org.opencv.osgi,
      and individual classes from org.opencv.core, org.opencv.imgproc,
      org.opencv.photo). See version control history for the full list.

2) ONNX Runtime (submodule, required runtime)
    - Project: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime
    - Path: external/onnxruntime (Git submodule)
    - License: MIT License
    - Notes: Built from source for Android (XNNPACK and NNAPI, Java bindings) via
      scripts/build_onnxruntime_android.sh. The resulting native libraries and
      Java JAR are integrated into app/jniLibs and app/libs respectively as part
      of the required ONNX Runtime support. The MIT license text is included at
      third_party_licenses/onnxruntime_LICENSE.txt.
    - Pinned build files (external/onnxruntime_pinned/):
      Three Gradle build files from the upstream ONNX Runtime repository
      (java/build-android.gradle, java/settings-android.gradle,
      java/gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.properties) have been copied and
      modified to enable building the Android AAR with JDK 21 and to keep
      versions aligned with the Make a Copy host project. The following
      changes were made compared to the upstream originals:
        * build-android.gradle:
          – Android Gradle Plugin updated from 7.4.2 to 8.12.0 (kept in sync
            with makeacopy gradle/libs.versions.toml).
          – compileSdkVersion raised from 34 to 36 (kept in sync with
            makeacopy app/build.gradle).
          – Nested `android { lintOptions }` block flattened to top-level
            `lintOptions` inside the `android` block.
          – Removed upstream code comments (QNN format notes, version-code
            format documentation, artifact-id comment, publish-repo comment,
            AAR header-packaging comment).
          – Reformatted indentation from tabs to spaces for consistency.
          – `task.doLast` closure in `whenTaskAdded` wrapped correctly to
            reference `task.archivePath`.
          – Added sync-marker comments referencing makeacopy configuration.
        * settings-android.gradle:
          – Added `pluginManagement` block with google(), mavenCentral(), and
            gradlePluginPortal() repositories (required by AGP 8.x).
          – Added sync-marker comment referencing makeacopy AGP version.
        * gradle-wrapper.properties:
          – Gradle distribution updated from 8.7 to 8.13 (kept in sync with
            makeacopy gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.properties).
          – SHA-256 checksum updated accordingly.
          – Added sync-marker comment referencing makeacopy wrapper.

